<#tt0058458-dbdumonteil>
	schema:about <#tt0058458>;
	schema:author "dbdumonteil";
	schema:dateCreated "Mon Dec 02 2002 00:00:00 GMT+0100 (Mitteleurop√§ische Normalzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 9;
	schema:headline " Harsh conclusion";
	schema:reviewBody "This Truffaut is more old cinema than new waveJean Desailly is unusual in Jules et Jim director's universe.He's certainly one of the greatest French actors I know but he's better with Jean Delannoy or Edouard Molinaro.Truffaut's touch is here anywayyou can feel it thru the fatherdaughter relationshipduring the scene when Desailly brings a classical music record to his little girl .The breakfast trail which the cat finds on this way will be here again in la nuit amricaine  day for night.A lot of details show the cine buff Truffaut wasnotably the restaurant called la Colinire the name of the mansion in Jean Renoir's la rgle du jeuthe room 813 is probably a nod to Maurice Leblanc and Arsne Lupin.The love triangle would have been be tritehad not Truffaut focused on the cheated wife Nelly Benedetti an offbeat move.The end of the movie is hers at the expense of the late Franoise Dorleac's pretty girl character.And the scene in the street with the man who treats her like a whore is woman's lib before its timewho do you think you are?take a good look at yourself!  this desperate woman screams.And the harsh conclusion heralds that of la marie tait en noir the bride wore black.0".

