<#tt0058458-bts1984>
	schema:about <#tt0058458>;
	schema:author "bts1984";
	schema:dateCreated "Sat Jun 02 2012 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleurop√§ische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 10;
	schema:headline " Delicious title";
	schema:reviewBody "This is the 4th film by mister Truffaut. Despite the success achieved with the previous films this one wasn't as well received. Part of the reason might have been because at the time the previous films were considered Nouvelle Vague and this one had a more conservative philosophy. It may have been that to a degree but it still has all those little details so Truffautish.'La peau douce' is an interesting title. It sounds appealing and it is also quite suggestive  it makes you think of sexuality sensuality the sweetness and softness of the female skin.The story is from the type I've been there before telling the tale of Pierre Lachenay a writer and lecturer. He is married with an attractive woman Franca and he's got a daughter Sabine. During a travel to Lisbon he meets the charming and beautiful air hostess Nicole and soon they have a love affair. But not everything goes right and there's a tragedy in store for Pierre in the ending. This film is like a love triangle but in a different way than 'Jules et Jim'. Even though Pierre is a ladies's man we sympathize with the character rather than loathe him. He is not a bad person but he is immature. His problem is weakness of character. Sometimes he is very nice but other times he is so insensitive and selfish. The harsh ending is the sign that Pierre pays with his life for his mistakes even though I wouldn't have wanted to see him getting killed.Jean Desailly is an interesting actor and he portrays Pierre Lauchenay very well. The gorgeous Franoise Dorlac who sadly passed away early and under tragic circumstances is great as the lovely Nicole. Nelly Benedetti is pretty good as Franca and so is Sabine Haudepin as Sabine. I also like Daniel Ceccaldi as Clment  his acting is great fun even the character himself is rather amusing. Filming is generally great cinematography is pure Truffaut good the soundtrack is great especially the sweet Toy Symphony by Leopold Mozart the plot is quite interesting.Title in Portugal 'Angstia'.".

