<#tt0058458-flipshoes>
	schema:about <#tt0058458>;
	schema:author "flipshoes";
	schema:dateCreated "Wed Sep 28 2005 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleurop√§ische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 8;
	schema:headline " A beautiful gem";
	schema:reviewBody "Very poetic early Truffaut but already at his best. This story of a middleaged intellectual man who certainly should not have too much to complain about in his life but wants to give it a try for whatever reasons midlife crisis? vanity? play instinct? the beginnings of some sort of amour fou on his part? thus bringing about a catastrophe is brought to the screen in a powerful and masterly way.It's all been described in large part by other users so far Raoul Coutard's impressive blackandwhite cinematography the acting by Dorlac Desailly and Benedetti it all fitted very well.What's more to mention however is a beautiful soundtrack by Georges Delerue in my opinion a true masterpiece of film scoring with a haunting main theme. This is really a film I shall keep in my heart for a long time. I certainly prefer it to Jules et Jim.".

