<#tt0058458-202222>
	schema:about <#tt0058458>;
	schema:author "202222";
	schema:dateCreated "Mon Jul 12 2004 00:00:00 GMT+0200 (Mitteleurop√§ische Sommerzeit)";
	schema:reviewRating 9;
	schema:headline " Could have done better....";
	schema:reviewBody "I'm a huge Truffaut fan the ending of 'Les Quatre Cent Coups' is perhaps the greatest scene of all time but this disappointed me. It became Truffaut's 'let's satirise the bourgeoisie' film. But without the intense political agenda of Godard with whom he collaborated on 'A Bout de Souffle' the satire is hollow. Ultimately it's a disappointingly conventional film and perhaps represents the difficulty in much of Truffaut's work  he never quite worked out what sort of director he was. He takes a simplistic and in some ways cliched plot which is fine but it doesn't become the starting off point for anything deeper. Truffaut can be capable of greatness but here he misses by a long way.".

